  "text": "As noted in our introduction, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] have already reported quantitative advantages in the fit of a knowledge-rich VR model that uses an ideal-observer decision rule. One purpose of the present work was to provide converging tests of [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] findings in our modified paradigm. In addition, although we expected knowledge-rich versions of the VR model to be able to account for the main qualitative data pattern that was the focus of our design, it was an open question how such models would fare in quantitative comparisons with our mixed-state model. We pursue these questions in the present section.",
